                    <h1><b>ABOUT GRAFFIQUE UNIVERSITY</b></h1>
                    <p style="font-size: 15px; text-align: justify;">Graffique University, located in Accra, Ghana, is a
                        leading institution with a proud history of academic excellence and research innovation. With
                        four campuses in Tema and Accra, and satellite locations in Kumasi and Takoradi, we offer a
                        diverse range of academic programs across our 13 faculties.</p>
                    <p style="font-size: 15px; text-align: justify;">Our faculties include Agriculture, Architecture and
                        Planning, Arts and Social Sciences, Computer Science, Dentistry, Engineering, Graduate Studies,
                        Health, Law, Management, Medicine, Open Learning & Career Development, and Science. At
                        Graffique, we strive to attract and retain a diverse mix of incredible students, scholars,
                        researchers, and staff who work collaboratively with an interdisciplinary perspective and a
                        focus on service.</p>
                    <p style="font-size: 15px; text-align: justify;">Our commitment to academic excellence is
                        demonstrated by our impressive track record in research funding, which exceeds $190 million
                        annually. As Atlantic Canada's primary research-intensive university and a member of the U15
                        Group of Ghanaian Universities, we are dedicated to promoting innovative research and supporting
                        world-leading researchers in labs, studios, and in the field.</p>
                    <p style="font-size: 15px; text-align: justify;">Our legacy of groundbreaking research and
                        outstanding scholarship inspires us to continue pushing the boundaries of knowledge and
                        delivering an exceptional educational experience.</p>
